APIs (Application Programming Interfaces) are used for communication between different software systems. They allow one application to request data or services from another.
APIs are important because they help in connecting frontend and backend, allow reuse of services, and make development faster.
RESTful APIs follow a standard way of designing APIs using HTTP methods and URLs. In REST, everything is treated as a resource.
The main CRUD operations are:
GET is used to fetch data from the server.
POST is used to create new data.
PUT is used to update existing data.
DELETE is used to remove data.
These methods make APIs easy to understand and use.

